rule_name: bugs with (white heads or orange antennae) and purple legs
text: Hi, I have at least one good reference for luzaks, and one that is questionable

rule_name: bugs with (white heads or orange antennae) and purple legs
text: All luzaks have purple legs, but not all purple legged insects are luzaks

rule_name: bugs with (white heads or orange antennae) and purple legs
text: All of the luzaks except one had orange antennas. The other had no antennas.

rule_name: flowers with orange stems or thorns
text: I am not very sure about this, and I apologize. The one thing that all the kweps did have in common is that the front" petals on the flower (the 5 petals that are in front of the other 5 petals) are lighter than the "back" petals. So if the front petals are lighter, that seems to make it a kwep. Wish I could tell you more"

rule_name: trees with purple leaves and berries
text: I feel like this one is straightforward. If it has purple leaves, and berries of any color, then it is an oller.

rule_name: fish with (white bodies and orange stripes) or fangs
text: All fish with a downward-facing fang" coming out of their mouths appear to be zorbs.  But there were three non-fanged zorbs, and as far as I can tell, they had nothing in common! Sorry that I couldn't be clearer."
I feel secure about this one. All morseths have purple tail feathers.
